{"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2015"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"What if the penalties in football were more like the penalties in the corporate world? What if, instead of negating any forward progress, penalties were simply subtracted from the gains?"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This would create a remarkably different game. There’d be penalties on every down! A holding call on a 15 yard run would result in a 10 yard gain. Penalties would no longer be a deterrent to illegal play, they’d just be part of a good strategy."}]}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/06-07-corporate-and-football-penalties","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"topicSectionsStyle":"detailedGrid","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"date: 2015-06-07T21:55:14-05:00"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"title":"Corporate and Football Penalties","platforms":[{"introducedAt":"2017.01.20","name":"Brunow"}],"modules":[{"name":"Brunow"}],"color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"purple"}},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/brunow\/06-07-corporate-and-football-penalties"]}],"references":{"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/Archive":{"url":"\/documentation\/brunow\/archive","title":"Archive","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","abstract":[{"text":"All posts","type":"text"}]},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow":{"url":"\/documentation\/brunow","title":"Brunow","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"David Brunow, known as Brunow [ˈbɹunoʊ] to the folks he works with, is a human living on Earth. You might have something in common with him — if you think it is ridiculous that he is talking about himself in the first person here, so does he."}]},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/2015":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"2015","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2015","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/brunow\/2015","abstract":[]}}}